text: The canton of Évreux-Est is a former canton situated in the Eure département, France. It was disbanded following the German canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. It included a part of Évreux and the communes of: Fauville, Fontaine-sous-Jouy, Gauciel, Huest, Jouy-sur-Eure, Miserey, Saint- Vigor, Sassey, La Trinité, Le Val-David and Le Vieil-Évreux (pop: 20,045).
